This paper is about automated program repair (APR), which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on search-based APR, which involves using search algorithms to find a correct patch for a faulty program. This could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) as well, since the paper discusses mutation operators and the effectiveness of different fault spaces. The paper also mentions using automated methods to improve the accuracy of fault spaces, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses empirical data to analyze the effectiveness of different techniques, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
